OL,6,F"On the 1-to-5 scale of probability
OL,7,Fthey used, I had scored a wretched 4,"
OL,8,Fhe added.
OL,10,FHowever, the author recalled the
OL,11,Fnormal prostate cancer PSA test, which
OL,12,Fchecks the amount of prostate-specific
OL,13,Fantigen in your blood, showed a
OL,14,Fdifferent story.
OL,16,FHe wrote: "The PSA number on my blood
OL,17,Ftest was low: 2.1. This would normally
OL,18,Fbe read to mean 'no prostate problem'.
OL,19,FBut the MRI results said cancer
OL,20,Flikely."
