OL,6,FAfter seeking the opinion of a second
OL,7,Furologist, he was told that a urinary-
OL,8,Ftract infection he had recently been
OL,9,Ftreated for "might be responsible" for
OL,10,Fthe bump on his prostate.
OL,12,FHe recalled that as he waited for
OL,13,Ffurther tests to give him a conclusive
OL,14,Fanswer, the doctor tried to reassure
OL,15,Fhim that if it was prostate cancer, it
OL,16,F"spreads slowly".
OL,18,FAfter two months, he received the all-
OL,19,Fclear he had been waiting for.
